        {
          "renderType": "container",
          "maxWidth": "xs",
          "tag": "div",
          "richTextStyles": true,
          "content": [
            {
              "renderType": "rich-text",
              "tag": "p",
              "content": "The flag motif continued on the topic landing page in the timeline layout of topics. Each colour also corresponds to the background colour for the individual topic pages to keep our use of colour intentional. It was also a great way to distinguish topics from each other as they are each unique pages of content. We also adjusted the original colours to have sufficient contrast for accessibility."
            },
            {
              "renderType": "rich-text",
              "tag": "p",
              "content": "As mentioned before, we wanted to be intentional about our use of colour. We chose dark blue to be the main colour and maroon red as the secondary colour as a nod to the American flag and also simultaneous symbols of peace, justice and sacrifice that are key parts of Why We Serve. These colours being darker and more subdued also helped make the images on the site really stand out for viewers to appreciate and lended to an overall elegant and cinematic look."
            }
